<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><b><font style="font-size: 24px;">Eclipse with Tomcat</font></b></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Installing the Tomcat</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Required Software:</font></span></div><div><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic; text-decoration: underline;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Web, XML, Java EE and OSGi Enterprise Development:</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">•</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Eclipse Java Web Developer Tools</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Step 1</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: Download the Tomcat from </span><a href="http://www.tomcat.apache.org" style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">www.tomcat.apache.org</a><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"> and extract some where in your PC.</span></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">            We will be using the version Tomcat 7.0.xx</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Step 2</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: Windows --&gt;  Open Perspective --&gt; Web  ( If you don't see "Web" click on "Other...")</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Step 3</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: Eclipse --&gt; Preferences --&gt; Server --&gt; Runtime Enviroments and click "Add"</span></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">     Choose "Apache --&gt; Apache Tomcat v7.0"  </font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">             Tomcat installation directory is where you extracted the Tomcat in Step1:</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">             ( Users/khasanov/Dev-Software/Tomcat/</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">apache-tomcat-7.0.xx</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">)</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Step 4</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: In the Web Perspective you should be able to see "Server" palet in the below. If you don't see it, you can </span></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">    always get it from going "Window --&gt; Show View"</font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">            Now highlight the Server and add the Tomcat .</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Step 5</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: Testing. Visit </span><a href="http://127.0.0.1:8080" style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">http://127.0.0.1:8080</a></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(255, 38, 0);">HTTP Error 404</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"> : First, stop your Tomcat, then double click your server, click </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier;">Server Locations</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"> and check </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Courier;">Use Tomcat Installation (takes control of Tomcat installation):</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><en-media hash="4877f26acb3bc2ce64e2faf8d63008a8" type="image/tiff" /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">How to Create a Dynamic Web Apps </font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Step 1: Windows --&gt; Open Prespective --&gt; Java EE  ( If you don't see "Java EE" click on "Other..." and search for it)</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Step 2: File --&gt; New --&gt; Dynamic Web Project  ( Again, if you don't see this option, search for it in "Others")</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Project name</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: MyWebApp</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Project Location</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"> (default): /Users/khasanov/codes/Java/eclipse/workplace/MyWebApp</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Target runtime</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: Apache Tomcat v7.0</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Dynamic web module version</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: 2.5   ( defaul was 3.0)</span></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">        Next --&gt; Next --&gt; Finish</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">        Now you should see the new project in the Project Explorer (left panel), called "MyWebApp" </font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">                                               </font></span></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">All our new Java classes will go under "Java Resources" --&gt; "src"</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; text-decoration: underline;">Step 3</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: Lets create a package first: Right click on "src" --&gt; New --&gt; Package </span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">     </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Name</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: ca.karshi.java.examples.</span><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic;">MyWebApp</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"><font style="font-size: 18px;">Step 4: To Create a Servlet higlight the package name and right click New --&gt; Servlet</font></span></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">     </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Name</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">: </span><span style="font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-style: italic;">MyWebServlet       </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">( Remember : We are creating a Java class  "MyWebServlet.java")</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">             Make sure that you have selected "doPost" and "doGet"  before you click </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; font-weight: bold;">Finish</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">. </span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><br /></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;">Step 5: We want to modify the </span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(20, 114, 255);">doGet()</span><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica;"> method of the "MyWebServlet.java" class:</span></font></div><div><font style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(